Class Implementor

  • java.lang.Object
    • info.kgeorgiy.ja.dubrovin.implementor.Implementor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Impler, JarImpler
    public class Implementor
extends Object
implements JarImpler
    Implementation of JarImpler. Generates .java and .jar files, which implement given class or interface.

      • main

        public static void main​(String[] args)
        Gets arguments from console, checks arguments, and then calls needed implementation.
        • 2 arguments - className and rootPath - creates .java file by invoke implement(java.lang.Class<?>, java.nio.file.Path)
        • 3 arguments - -jar, className and jarPath - creates .jar file by invoke implementJar(java.lang.Class<?>, java.nio.file.Path)
        Parameters:
        args - arguments received by the code.

      • checkArguments

        private static void checkArguments​(String[] args)
                            throws ImplerException
        Checks the correctness of the received arguments. Checks if there is a null argument, if the number of arguments is 2 or 3 and if 3, checks first argument.
        Parameters:
        args - arguments received by the code.
        Throws:
        ImplerException - if
        • no arguments, or their number is incorrect.
        • one of the arguments is null.
        • 3 arguments, and the first one is not -jar".

      • implement

        public void implement​(Class<?> token,
                      Path root)
               throws ImplerException
        Creates .java file, which implement received token. Places result file in root directory. Result file name is token name + Impl.
        Specified by:
        implement in interface Impler
        Parameters:
        token - type token to create implementation for.
        root - root directory.
        Throws:
        ImplerException - if implementation failed, because
        • One of variables become null.
        • Can't create path directory.
        • Received class equals to array, enum or primitive type.
        • Received class is final or private.
        • No constructors found in token.
        • Something will go wrong with output file.

      • implementJar

        public void implementJar​(Class<?> token,
                         Path jarFile)
                  throws ImplerException
        Creates .jar file, which implement received token. Invokes implement(java.lang.Class<?>, java.nio.file.Path), buildJar(java.lang.Class<?>, java.nio.file.Path, java.nio.file.Path). Creates temporary directory during the generation, then deletes it.
        Specified by:
        implementJar in interface JarImpler
        Parameters:
        token - type token to create implementation for.
        jarFile - target .jar file.
        Throws:
        ImplerException - if implementation failed, because
        • One of variables become null.
        • Can't create path directory.
        • If tmp path is invalid
        • Something will go wrong with jar output file.
        • Something will go wrong with clean tmp directory
